section.p:
This is the basic choice you will have to make for your output. You can use the @page rule like this: @page { 
  size: us-letter;
}The page sizes can be selected by name, like: A4, A3, US-LEGAL (these are case insensitive), or, if you are planning to print on a non-standard sheet, you can specify the width and height: @page { 
  size: 5in 7in;
}

section.codeblock:
@page :left {
  border-right: 0.5in solid yellow;
}

@page :right {
  border-left: 0.5in solid yellow;
}

@page {
  size: A4;
  margin: 1in;
}

@page table-landscape-page {
  size: landscape;
  margin: 0.5in;
}

table {
  page: table-landscape-page;
}
